class.javadoc:
Returns a contextual shaper for the provided Unicode range(s). The Latin-1 (EUROPEAN) digits will be converted to the decimal digits corresponding to the range of the preceding text, if the range is one of the provided ranges. The shaper uses {@codedefaultContext} as the starting context.
ranges the specified Unicode ranges
defaultContext the starting context, such as{@code NumericShaper.Range.EUROPEAN}
a contextual shaper for the specified Unicode ranges.
NullPointerExceptionif {@code ranges} or {@code defaultContext} is {@code null}
